# ClaudeTube Agent Integration

When the user shares a YouTube URL, asks to play/watch a video, or wants something queued while coding, use ClaudeTube.

## Preferred method: agent inbox

Write a JSON command to `.claudetube/inbox.json` in the workspace root. The extension watches this file and executes immediately.

```json
{ "action": "play", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID" }
```

Multiple commands in one write:

```json
[
  { "action": "play", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID" },
  { "action": "setLayout", "layout": "mini" }
]
```

### Actions

| Action | Fields | Description |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| `play` | `url` or `videoId`, optional `title` | Play now in sidebar |
| `enqueue` | `url` or `videoId`, optional `title` | Add to queue |
| `toggle` | — | Play/pause |
| `show` | — | Focus ClaudeTube sidebar |
| `clearQueue` | — | Clear queue |
| `setLayout` | `layout`: `compact` \| `theater` \| `mini` | Change layout |
| `setPlaybackRate` | `rate`: 0.25–2 | Set speed |

## Alternative: shell helper

```bash
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh play "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID"
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh enqueue "https://youtu.be/VIDEO_ID"
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh toggle
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh layout mini
```

## Alternative: VS Code commands

If terminal access to Cursor CLI is available:

- `claudetube.playUrl` — play URL
- `claudetube.enqueue` — add to queue
- `claudetube.togglePlay` — play/pause (`Cmd+Shift+Y`)
- `claudetube.show` — open sidebar (`Cmd+Shift+0`)

## Behavior

- After writing inbox.json, tell the user the video is loading in the ClaudeTube sidebar.
- For tutorials the user is following, prefer `mini` layout with `setPlaybackRate` 1.25–1.5 when they want to move faster.
- If embedding fails (owner disabled), suggest opening in browser via the player UI.
